    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with **Pete Crow-Armstrong** serving as our highest-upside play (82.13). Facing the vulnerable xERA of 5.52 from the opposing starter, **Pete Crow-Armstrong** benefits from a massive 19% boost in SP skill valuation and favorable winds, making him an elite start despite batting in the lower third of the order. Similarly, **Junior Caminero** (73.53) and **Trea Turner** (68.86) provide the core stability of our lineup; **Trea Turner** leverages his leadoff positioning to maximize his stolen base potential\u2014our league's most critical currency\u2014while **Junior Caminero** faces a favorable platoon dynamic against an opposing arm whose peripherals suggest a high-contact environment for our hitters.\n\nThe most difficult decision on today's board was the exclusion of **Victor Scott II** (39.50). While his speed profile is inherently valuable to the Zebras' roster strategy, his matchup against a sub-3.50 xERA arm suppressed his projection just enough to dip below our 40.0 floor. We are prioritizing the higher scoring floors of **Hyeseong Kim** and **Chase Meidroth** to maintain our competitive edge in the 5x5 categories. Note that while **Caleb Durbin** carries a pedestrian raw projection, his 16% park factor adjustment makes him a viable plug-in at 3B, providing a much-needed boost in high-offense conditions. With **Christian Yelich** and **Lars Nootbaar** remaining sidelined on the IL, we continue to rely on the depth of **Gary Sanchez**, **Luke Raley**, **Josh Smith**, **Jerar Encarnacion**, **Carson Benge**, and **Luis Pena** to monitor pinch-hit opportunities should any of our starters struggle against these early-season pitching rotations.",
